n  extends: [\n    'eslint:recommended',\n    'plugin:@typescript-eslint/recommended',\n  ],\n  parserOptions: {\n    ecmaVersion: 2022,\n    sourceType: 'module',\n  },\n  rules: {\n    '@typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars': ['error', { argsIgnorePattern: '^_', varsIgnorePattern: '^_' }],\n  },\n  env: {\n    node: true,\n    es2022: true,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN REQUIREMENTS SUMMARY\n\n#### **WAVE 1 (No dependencies)**\n\n1. **markdown-ext** (`/src/plugins/markdown-ext.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n   - Hook: `transformContent`\n   - Converts markdown to HTML, adds footnotes support, converts :::admonition containers\n\n2. **asset-pipeline** (`/src/plugins/asset-pipeline.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n   - Hook: `transformContent`\n   - Rewrites `./` URLs to `/assets/`, maintains manifest in `ctx.data['asset-manifest']`\n\n3. **syntax-highlight** (`/src/plugins/syntax-highlight.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`\n   - Hook: `transformContent`\n   - Adds `highlighted` class and `data-language` attribute to code blocks\n\n4. **taxonomy** (`/src/plugins/taxonomy.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createTaxonomyPlugin()`\n   - Hooks: `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n   - Builds tag index in `ctx.data['taxonomy-tags']`, generates tag pages in output\n\n#### **WAVE 2 (Depend on Wave 1)**\n\n5. **rss-feed** (`/src/plugins/rss-feed.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createRssFeedPlugin()`\n   - Dependencies: `markdown-ext`, `taxonomy`\n   - Hook: `afterBuild`\n   - Generates RSS 2.0 feed at `feed.xml`\n\n6. **search-index** (`/src/plugins/search-index.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createSearchIndexPlugin()`\n   - Dependencies: `markdown-ext`, `syntax-highlight`\n   - Hook: `afterBuild`\n   - Generates search index JSON at `search-index.json`\n\n#### **WAVE 3 (Depend on Wave 2)**\n\n7. **sitemap** (`/src/plugins/sitemap.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createSitemapPlugin()`\n   - Dependencies: `taxonomy`, `rss-feed`\n   - Hook: `afterBuild`\n   - Generates XML sitemap at `sitemap.xml`\n\n8. **dev-server** (`/src/plugins/dev-server.ts`)\n   - Factory: `createDevServerPlugin()`\n   - Dependencies: `asset-pipeline`, `search-index`\n   - Hook: `afterBuild`\n   - Generates dev server config in `ctx.data['dev-server-config']`\n\n---\n\n### 6. PLUGIN SYSTEM MECHANICS\n\nAll plugins must:\n- Export a factory function named `create{PluginName}Plugin()` that returns a `Plugin` object\n- Have `name`, `version`, `dependencies` properties\n- Have `hooks` property with optional `beforeBuild`, `transformContent`, `afterBuild` methods\n- `transformContent` receives `(file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext)` and returns `Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile`\n- `beforeBuild` and `afterBuild` receive `(ctx: BuildContext)` and return `Promise<void> | void`\n- Can store/retrieve shared data via `ctx.data` Map\n- Can write output files via `ctx.output` Map\n- Plugin execution order determined by topological sort of dependencies\n\n---\n\n### 7. EXISTING PLUGINS STATUS\n\nCurrently: **0 plugins implemented** (only `.gitkeep` in `/workspace/src/plugins/`)\n\nNeed to create all 8 plugins to pass the test suite (60 new tests + existing 15 core tests = 75 total)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: adb253e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 38291\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 49210</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8d72ee18-876f-4ac5-9b4e-e758f8087036","uuid":"ce32888a-54c3-430c-9b63-d28d06f3353f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory structure\n2. All files in src/core/ - read every file completely\n3. All test files in tests/ - read every file completely\n4. The package.json and tsconfig.json\n5. Any existing plugin files or plugin directories\n\nRead ALL files completely - don't summarize. I need exact interfaces, types, function signatures, and test expectations.","agentId":"adb253e","content":[{"